    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-01T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-01T09:00:00-05:00" n="922"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d922">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/542: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-01T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 1, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 1—12:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Your No. 18, March 31, 6 p.m.<note n="22" xml:id="d922fn22">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Trade agreement was signed at noon today. Publicity arrangements have been
                        made in accordance with your third paragraph. Textual details are given in
                        separate telegram.</item>
                    <pb facs="0872" n="866" xml:id="pg_866"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>I take occasion to record warmest appreciation of patience and ability of
                        Kelley and Gillespie in bringing to a successful conclusion these
                        negotiations extending over almost a year.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For text of reciprocal trade agreement and supplementary notes, signed at
                        Ankara, April 1, 1939, see Department of State Executive Agreement Series
                        No. 163, or 54 Stat. 1870.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
